text: Kennebec County is a county in the state of Maine, in the United States. As of the 2020 census, the county's population was 123,642. The county seat is Augusta, the state capital. The county was created on February 20, 1799. == References == Category:18th-century establishments in Maine Category:1799 establishments in the United States Category:Maine counties
title: Kennebec County, Maine
